Here's a very high-level overview and simplified approach to implement such a game in C. Note that I'll be using console-based graphics for simplicity. More complex games might require a graphics library like SDL, where animations can be handled more intricately.

This example assumes that a single glyph file can be used to create a "frame" for snake animation. For a fully animated snake, you would need each segment of the snake to be a separate image.

